tmfs

Time Machine File System is a read-only virtual filesystem which helps you to
read your Apple's time machine backup.

Enjoy!


Time Machine structure :

${hfs_root}/.HFS+ Private Directory Data/dir_${node_id}/ <- real data
${hfs_root}/Backups.backupdb/$comp_name/${date}/Macintosh HD/ <- snapshot root
${hfs_root}/Backups.backupdb/$comp_name/${date}/Macintosh HD/.../File with hardlink count > XXXX => hardlink count = node_id


Our representation :

/${comp_name}/${date}/${Real root}
